socialmediaposting.articlebody: System Update: Due to maintenance elsewhere, there will be reduced functionality for a short while up to and including the the 9th of July. Watch for updates a bit closer to this date on resumption...
Meteogram update … It is now possible to request a meteogram for any BGA turn point. This can be found here: https://rasp.stratus.org.uk/index.php/custom-meteograms… Forecasts are done...
Yes … it works fine for me (Win10 laptop with Firefox or Edge and iPad/IOS). I’ll be adding a timer countdown shortly.
Meteogram Update … having had requests for custom meteograms (i.e. any turn point), a working application is now being tested. If all goes well, it should be available in the next week.
Update on Track Average functions … The code for the graphs on the track have been refreshed and both table and track are now are available is an image
System Update: The soundings function is now back and working as expected. Do check the date is as expected on the top of the plot. All models should be updated by midday.
System Update: The soundings function is not working as expected, so has temporary been disabled while the issue is investigated. Target is to be reinstated Monday 4th March.
Wishing all a Happy Christmas despite the weather today being wet, windy with a bit of snow across parts of Scotland.
Systems update: The UK 4km and 12km models are now up to date. The viewers for the 2km models are disabled for today until refreshed overnight. The remaining models for Wales, Scotland and...
Systems update: Due to hosting issues, model runs for Friday 22nd have not completed so all forecasts are out of date. Restarts should complete later today for this evening. Watch for updates...
Second Monday update. There is a new fix in place for Meteograms so that the wind/rain and cloud is now identified for the entire week. Here’s Lasham for Thursday (it’s currently looking...
While some maintenance takes place, a few options will not be available until tomorrow (Monday). Watch out for further updates when all functions are back.
Monday Update. The updates have completed and usual functions are now available.
Mon(+0) high CAPE levels above 3000J today with heavy rain from 16:00 in the indicated areas of England and into mid/North Wales
Notice of platform and hosting moves: The hosting provider has outlined a data centre move for their hosting services on the 16th of May. It is stated as transparent, but there could be some...
In an unexpected change, the hosting supplier has now stated they are bringing forward the network change to tonight, Sunday the 14th of May. Access to the RASP UI will be limited from 18:00...
The ‘Track Average’ page is unavailable due to a configuration issue. Apologies for this. The target is to have resolved this coming week, so watch here for an update when available again.
Systems update 10/3/23 - after hosting migration a few days ago, some DNS changes are required today that may affect mapping and viewers. Graphs are working normally. Watch for an update later...
DNS changes have been completed, so mapping and content delivery should operate as normal. If you want to get in touch, the contact email address has also changed, so use the ‘contact us’...
8/3/23: There was an overnight change (migration) by the hosting provider which has broken a lot of scripts. Bear with us while this is sorted out.
10:30 8/3/23: Most functions are now working normally, but three need further work. If you spot anything odd, do get in touch. Further update around 20:00 this evening.
